FBIS4-67338 "jptdd022__l94103" JPRS-TDD-94-022-L JPRS Narcotics 15 May 1994 WEST EUROPE SWITZERLAND Cocaine From Argentina Seized at Chiasso Station Cocaine From Argentina Seized at Chiasso Station BR1605132994 Bern ATSA/SDAA Database in French 1944 GMT 15 May 94 BR1605132994 Bern ATSA/SDAA Database French BFN [Article signed UC: "Eight Kilos of Cocain Seized in Chiasso"] [Text] Chiasso, 15 May (ATS/ANSA) -- Eight kilos of cocaine worth 7.2 million Swiss francs were seized during the night from Saturday [14 May] to Sunday [15 May] onboard the Zurich-Rome train at Chiasso station. The drugs were found inside the suitcase of a 28-year-old Polish national, who claimed he did not know what was inside the suitcase. According to the customs service, the cocaine came from Argentina and was bound for Rome. On 24 March, 11 kg of cocaine from Argentina were seized. Three individuals, two Italian brothers and one Latin American national, were arrested in that seizure.
